BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260326T233000Z
DTEND:20260327T003000Z
LOCATION:AUDITORIUM
GEO:39.168443;-86.517858
SUMMARY:Neil deGrasse Tyson
DESCRIPTION:Science ambassador Neil deGrasse Tyson returns to Bloomington
  for the first time since 2017 and will present a lecture titled "An Astr
 ophysicist Goes to the Movies – Part II."  From the Wizard of Oz to Mar
 y Poppins to 2001: A Space Odyssey to Harry Potter to A Bug's Life\, it w
 ill be an entertaining and enlightening review of all the science that ou
 r favorite movies got wrong\, combined with some of the stuff they got ri
 ght. The discussion will incorporate the latest films as well as some cla
 ssics that you may not have known had any science in them at all.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Science ambassador Neil deGrasse Tyson 
 returns to Bloomington for the first time since 2017 and will present a l
 ecture titled "An Astrophysicist Goes to the Movies – Part II."</p><p> 
  From the <em>Wizard of Oz</em> to <em>Mary Poppins</em> to <em>2001: A S
 pace Odyssey</em> to <em>Harry Potter</em> to <em>A Bug's Life\,</em> it 
 will be an entertaining and enlightening review of all the science that o
 ur favorite movies got wrong\, combined with some of the stuff they got r
 ight. The discussion will incorporate the latest films as well as some cl
 assics that you may not have known had any science in them at all.</p>
UID:20260326T233000Z-2031523@events.iu.edu
